==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|non}} {{term|lypta}} (Danish {{term|løfte}}) <ref>[http://ordnet.dk/ods/opslag?id=497366 Etymology of the verb] in [[:da:ODS|ODS]]: "'''''eng. lift fra nord.'''''"</ref>, cognates include German {{term|lüften}}

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|lĭft}}, {{IPA|/lɪft/}}, {{SAMPA|/lIft/}}
* {{audio|en-us-lift.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*: {{rhymes|ɪft}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{UK}} Mechanical [[device]] for [[vertically]] [[transporting]] goods or people between [[floors]] in a [[building]]; an [[elevator]].
#: ''Take the '''lift''' to the fourth floor.''
# The act of transporting someone in a vehicle; a [[ride]]; a [[trip]].
#: ''He gave me a '''lift''' to the bus station.''
# An upward [[force]], such as the force that keeps [[aircraft]] [[aloft]].
# (''measurement'') the difference in [[elevation]] between the upper pool and lower pool of a [[waterway]], separated by [[lock]].

====Synonyms====
* [[elevator]] (1)
* [[ride]] (2)
* [[uplift]] (3)

